data.description: Spanish style home built in 1936 has original hardwood floors, large arched front window and lots of original charm. The living room has an updated fireplace and arched entryways from the Living room to the dining area, and it includes a beautiful chandelier. Use your garden kitchen window to grow your fresh herbs, plus there is a bonus room off the kitchen that you can use as a breakfast nook or an office. Also included in the upstairs are two bedrooms, and one full bathroom that was recently remodeled. Need more room? Downstairs has additional living space, full bathroom, and bedroom(s) with its own entrance. A tandem garage is downstairs along with the laundry area. The backyard has been recently updated to include a tiled barbeque counter and matching floor, with plenty of room for family and friends to gather. Easy low maintenance landscape, plus some mature fruit trees. Live in one and use the other as an in-law-unit downstairs. This home has lots to offer and plenty of possibilities. In addition, new roof installed in August of 2023, updates, and repairs, this home is ready for you to move in and enjoy. Not far from shopping, freeways 780,80, 29, Vallejo Ferry Terminal and Benicia State Park.
